26/07/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Tulay Tugcu was appointed as the new president of Turkey's Constitutional Court on Monday (25 July), becoming the first woman assigned to the post. Tugcu was elected after six of the 11 members of the Court's panel of judges voted in favour of her nomination. (NTV, Turks.US - 26/07/05; TurkishPress.com - 25/07/05) 
